THE BASICS

What Is Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy?
Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy (HBOT) delivers 100% oxygen at increased
atmospheric pressure inside a pressurized chamber.
At 2.0 atmospheres of pressure, your lungs absorb significantly more oxygen than at
normal air pressure. This oxygen-rich blood reaches tissues throughout your body —
supporting recovery, reducing inflammation, and promoting cellular repair in ways that
normal breathing simply can''t achieve.

YOUR PLAN

Your HBOT Membership
Consistent sessions are key to getting the most out of hyperbaric therapy.


4 Sessions / Month
Your membership includes 4 in-clinic HBOT sessions per 30-day rolling period. We
recommend spacing them throughout the month for optimal benefit.

30-Day Rolling Period
Your membership renews every 30 days from your start date. Sessions reset each
period — unused sessions do not roll over.

YOUR VISIT

What to Expect
Each session is straightforward and relaxing. Here''s the flow.

1

Check In
Arrive at the clinic and check in with our team. We''ll confirm your session and get
you set up.

2

Enter the Chamber
You''ll be guided into the hyperbaric chamber. Get comfortable — you can relax,
read, or rest during your session.

3

60-Minute Session
The chamber pressurizes to 2.0 atm while you breathe concentrated oxygen. You
may feel mild pressure in your ears as the chamber pressurizes — this is normal and
resolves quickly.


4

Post-Session
The chamber depressurizes gradually. You''re free to go about your day immediately
— no downtime needed.

TIPS

Getting the Most Out of HBOT
Stay Hydrated
Drink plenty of water before and after each session. Hydration helps your body
circulate and absorb the extra oxygen more effectively.

Be Consistent
The benefits of HBOT build over time. Aim for one session per week to maintain
steady progress throughout your membership period.

Wear Comfortable Clothing
Loose, comfortable clothing works best. Avoid anything with metal zippers or
buttons that could be uncomfortable during pressurization.

Skip Lotions and Perfumes
Avoid applying lotions, oils, or perfumes before your session. These products can
interact with the concentrated oxygen environment.


SAFETY

Important Safety Information
Contraindications:
✕ Untreated ear or sinus infections
✕ Severe claustrophobia
✕ Pregnancy
✕ Certain lung conditions (e.g., untreated pneumothorax)
✕ Recent ear surgery

Possible Side Effects:
• Mild ear pressure or popping during pressurization
• Temporary lightheadedness after session
• Slight fatigue (typically resolves within hours)
Side effects are generally mild and short-lived. If you experience anything unusual or
persistent, let our team know.

